	<p>risk is relative.  <br />
<br />
a lvl 1 vs an orc pawn that cons yellow or red is risky<br />
a lvl 30 vs a spectre in the oasis of marr is risky<br />
a lvl 50 vs a trash mob in first tier PoP is risky<br />
<br />
and just because a guild has 70 in attendance doesn't mean it's a zerg fest.  if a raid is executed well no matter the numbers, it isn't a zerg.  if you just get the directions "Go! CHARGE!" and 70 people throw their bodies at a mob in hopes of killing it, that's a zerg</p>
	
	
	
