<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Kandailu</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Junior Member<br />
	
	
	<br />
	Joined: Oct 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>As we all have opinions, here's mine..<br />
<br />
At this time there is no gear that can compare to time gear.. hell the common drops in tier1 time pretty much destroy any other item you can get.  But there is alot of effort involved in getting to that point.. rathe council is no joke, nor is the tedious process of getting up to there.  And as you move through the tiers in time it doesn't get any easier.. by no means can anyone just zerg their way through time, it all takes some degree of tact.  <br />
<br />
The thing is, everquest (along with basically any other mmorpg) is that it demands interaction with people.. otherwise it'd be like diablo where you just do stuff on your own, get some uber gear and share it with yourself.. there are people who don't have the time to invest in massively multiplayer games as much as others do, and because of that they'll always lag behind gearwise.. hell if everyone could get time-grade gear on their own, what would be the purpose of guilds?  it ultimately comes down to 1 thing, what you enjoy doing.  I used to just raid with a small group of friends, and we got the best that we could get, and we had fun doing it.. probably some of my better days of everquest were 1-2 group raids.  Just find what you enjoy, and do it.. cause no matter how good you are, somewhere down the road, someone will be better.. and who knows, maybe they're more miserable than people with un-comparable gear who just have a good time. <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /></p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Huntress Kandailu Raindancer<br />
65 Ranger<br />
Rallos Zek</div>
	
	
