<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>lyandras</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Senior Member<br />
	
	
	<br />
	Joined: Aug 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I always find it funny when people complain about raiding guilds getting better stuff than non raiding, and it isnt fair.<br />
<br />
When i joined my guild, we were taking 50 people and raiding the kail arena, working up to killing vindi. Failed a lot at first. Later we died many, many times to Tormax. Back then you could bind at the snowbank of kael, and we tried a zerg style attack once. The average amount of dying was about 4 bodies, with some people dying 12 times, when the guards camped the bindpoint.<br />
<br />
Later we moved up to 10 hour halls of testing raids, all so we could get gear to go on to NToV, and raid ST. Hell, i spent over a hundred raids getting up to the level of raiding Luclin!<br />
<br />
I cant even count the time it took to go through the luclin bosses, kill emp, then off to vt for a half dozen raids before pop came out.<br />
<br />
A couple years of raiding, hundreds of raids, thousands of hours spent. Along the way, we learned how to co ordinate, listen, figure out strategies for different mobs. <br />
<br />
Now that we are raiding time, we feel we are earning that reward. Without all the work before, no way could we have even attempted Time, were the keys just handed to us.<br />
<br />
<br />
For non raiders? The gear you can get now in the bazaar blows away the stuff i had for velious and luclin. Add in Ldon gear, and augments, and your far, far ahead of luclin/velious gear. I dont see the Have Nots being too far behind the Haves.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
