	<p>I think if non-raider A puts in 5 hours a day earning LDoN points and time-raider B puts in 5 hours a day raiding Time, the effort is the same. Both are working toward a goal. Eventually A will get that shiny new bp/sword/augmentation and B will kill Quarm. How is one's "work" any less valuable than the other? Goals are RELATIVE, guys. Player B's 5 hours a day is exactly the same effort as player A's. All that is different is what those hours are applied toward.<br />
