</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>to augment that post above:<br />
<br />
4 hr LDON Raid in 36 man raid win(60%?) = 30 AP, 6 drops, 4 of which are rotting (36 of 60 for us and counting!) I get 10% of an AA.<br />
<br />
4 hrs doing hards in 6 man grp = 6-8 wins and 600-800ish AP, assuming no rares per adventure, that's a miragul plate piece with 70hp/mana on it every 4 hrs. I get 3 AA min.<br />
<br />
So 2-3 raid drops to be split among 36 guys every 4 hrs, 1 piece that is in the 6-800AP range every 4 hrs for an LDoN grp. Plus 3 AA.<br />
<br />
Time? well last clearing was 4 hrs 19 min for us, with about 20 drops. For 72 (plus) people. And it's only up every 5 days. And I get about 30% of an AA. So using the same 4 hr comparison<br />
<br />
Time - 4 hrs 15/36 for an item (assuming something you need drops every go round), 30% of an AA, every 5 days.<br />
<br />
LDoN - 4 hrs, 6-800 AP Item per session, 5 days a week, 5 sessions. Nets 5 600-800AP items, 15 AA. No waiting, no DKP, no seniority, no "damn I already have that!"<br />
<br />
You do Time runs each and every time hoping that you might get something, but ultimately to make sure the guy beside you gets what you got, and you're hoping that he logs on to make sure you get what you need. I can't tell you how many times you log on for hrs, get no exp, get no cash/tradeskill/gems, get no items. But you kill the mob, your guildie gets something HE needs, and you go to bed feeling pretty good.<br />
<br />
If you are getting one drop a week, raiding every single night for 4 hrs a pop, in an 80 man guild, you are doing exceedingly well. That Time BP someone is wearing is not the result of one lucky run. It's weeks of effort. If he wants to augment it with a 40hp slot 8, to get a 20% upgrade on it, yeesh stop givin him grief.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Gheltire Leafshadow<br />
