	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I am confused by this. The original poster's beef was that Time gear was augmentable, so non-Time players were'nt going to "close in" on Time players?<br />
<br />
The mission statement of LDoN was not, to the best of my knowledge, to level the playing field between Time and non-Time players. No expansion is going to do that; what would be the point? What LDoN does is allow players to invest their playing time in getting elemental (I think, I wouldn't know) quality loot without the guild backup to actually get the Elemental flags. <br />
<br />
The sacrifice is XP; I hear tell of the amazing Elemental XP. Even Tier2+ planes XP beats LDoN XP.<br />
<br />
Personally I love LDoN, has allowed me to get some pretty amazing gear. Who'd have thunk a guildless low-playtimer such as myself would be able to get an 61ac Veng3 BP or 29ac 20sta 80hp arms.<br />
<br />
I don't begrudge Time-players their Type8 augs. Sheesh.</p>
	
	
	
