> The game "almost" achieved a balance between xp'ers and raiders.<br />
<br />
Why in the world they want to "balance" two things which are not out of proportion to each other?  There has never been a need to "balance" the equipment of raiders vs. not.  LDoN threw non-raiders the biggest bone in the history of EQ by allowing them to get outstanding equipment for zero effort on their own time.  <br />
<br />
Expansions are meant to be completed.  Look at their linear progression lines:<br />
<br />
Velious: Kael -> W/E ToV -> NToV<br />
Luclin: Junk -> Ssra -> VT<br />
PoP: T1 -> T2 -> T3 ... -> Time<br />
<br />
So, you want to penalize the people who acutally complete the expansions (as is the intent) by not allowing them the same options that people whos only use of PoP is to exp in BoT?  Nice.<br />
<br />
Get a clue.  There will always be strata in the player base - thats how it goes.  Unlike castes in society, however, any single person can jump up to a higher caste at any time by choosing to do so.  <br />
<br />
You want more?  Do what it takes.  In the mean time, dont target the big dogs - they play their game and you play yours.</p>
	
	
	
